cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for scene completion and object removal. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D scene reconstruction, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). The use of big data applications and machine learning techniques suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed algorithm for image completion involves edge matching and texture synthesis, which are techniques used in artificial intelligence and machine learning, respectively, indicating the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the proposed method, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
